Hello guys, had the same issue and solved it, but in my case it was a bit more related to BLoC rebuilding the TextField than to the TextField itself. The issue also haven't affected the field visually much: incorrect cursor position and micro-stutter when the messages drop to console.  

So, I had the BlocBuilder with a buildWhen set up. In the build I had the TextField and some simple logic that changed controller's initial value depending on the state. Really simple, something like this:
```
buildWhen: (previous, current) => previous.runtimeType != current.runtimeType,
builder: (context, state) {
  if (state is ReadSuccessExampleStorageState) _controller.text = state.value;
  if (state is ErrorExampleStorageState) _controller.text = state.error;
  if (state is DeleteSuccessExampleStorageState) _controller.text = 'value deleted';

  return CustomTextFormField(
  ...
```
I didn't use listener at first since builder should not have any undesired builds in this particular case. After some investigations I found out that build actually WAS happening when _unfocused_ field being tapped. I guess that happened because MediaQuery/Scaffold rebuilt on keyboard opening and invoked didChangeDependencies somewhere, since the buildWhen wasn't triggered during that parasitic build at all. 
Reworked it using BlocConsumer's listener, now the errors/warnings do not appear anymore.
Probably something like this could be reproduced with other state management or even with vanilla setState.
Hope my comment will help someone. This issue is pretty unobvious.

Btw this comment should not be treated as a solution - it's dealing with the consequence, not with the cause. Some undesired controller.text assignments should not be breaking the controller/textField like this.

